Methods
 List and explain the purpose of each method.
The build() method, builds the actual game using recursion and the checker() method, while puzzle() makes it into a playable game. 
Build() creates an already solved game using recursion
Puzzle() takes the parameter and removes the amount from the cells (81 total numbers/cells - 40 = Cells that appear when you load the game). Puzzle() is also used to update/print the current game, as it is used in print()

